node.text:
Today’s leg day workout!
Getting ready for my first show and I’m putting the work in!!!

Back Squat
✅30 reps 
10 reps (partial bottom) squat to bottom press 5" up then back down. 10 reps (partial top) start at top squat 5" down then back up. 10 reps full squats. Total of 30 reps.

✅15 reps
3/4 reps. Squat 3" below 90, then press back up to 3" below top. Repeat.

✅12 reps

Full slow reps 5 seconds down and 5 seconds up. 10 second rep speed.

✅12 reps
Double contraction bottom. Squat just below 90 then press up 5", then squat back down, then press back to top. This is 1 rep.

✅12 reps
Full reps. Drop weight then 12 more reps, then drop reps 10 more reps, drop weight, then 8 more reps. Total 42 reps.

This was the first exercise out of 8 🤪 will also do 15 min of cardio later 

One of my goal was to challenge myself and look the best I’ve ever look 1 year after bringing my  baby (if my body allowed it) … health first! Super excited for this challenge. I will be tracking my journey on my YouTube channel 😊⚡️

I’m being followed by one of the best coach ever and a legend in the sport from whom I am learning a tone about training for aesthetic and it’s been a blast so far @wattywatt01

I am beyond grateful and amazed to have been able to connect with such an amazing human being!

I hope you will enjoy this as much as I did

Challenge includes:
✅ Weekly Meal Plans
✅ Grocery ListWeekly
✅ Macronutrient Prescription
✅ Access to our private Facebook Group where I will be commenting and monitoring your progress.

$42 or free with Nutrition Membership. Link in profile to sign up! 👍

node.text:
Strength 
4 rounds
12 high pull
18 front raise
12 floor press
18 skull crushers

Workout
6 rounds
6 shoulder to overhead 
6 front squat
6 deadlift

Pelvic + core health
45 sec cat cow
45 sec open book
45 sec child pose
45 sec happy baby 
Cardio
30 min walk 
Finding a great and safe way to workout while being pregnant has been a lot more challenging than I anticipated... most doctor pretty much only tell you what not to do and the Informations via research is extremely confusing 
I feel so luck that I’ve found doctor @ladybirdpt to help me during my pregnancy and yes we are now building a program together to share all the tips and tricks to help other women like me that are really looking for help to stay healthy and active while creating a little miracle 🤗♥️🙌🏽 @feroce_fitness_

node.text:
The goal:
A fitness and nutrition program that helps build strong sustainable habits that supports my lifestyle and allows me to feel my best not only physically but also mentally 

@feroce_fitness_ 

A program that leaves you so broken that you can’t enjoy life is not what I am looking for

A program that leave you frustrated for not getting any results even tho you put the time in is not what I am looking for

A program that is mindful of the overall pressure we already face outside starting to take care of ourselves and gives me a strong plan to allow me to be my best self with what I have access to sounds amazing ⭐️🥰

Our new 30 days challenge is starting this Monday!!! We do weekly check in to help you keep going in the right direction and keep you accountable with our amazing community

…

I am finally starting to live my dream life! Travelling with my family and helping people ⭐️ it’s hard work but it’s worth it

node.text:
⭐️Wednesday Hump day ⭐️

Try this workout:
5 rounds
10 deadlift high pull
10 curtsey lunges
30 high knees

- Go as fast as you can while maintaining form.
- Choose a load that allows you to keep the weightlifting portion unbroken and keep the form Intact

Sumo deadlift high pull points of performance :
- brace your belly and arch your back through the full movement
- extend your hips, shrug and than high pull 
- elbow goes high and outside at the top

Curtsey lunges points of performance:
- chest up through the full movement
- front knees stay over or behind front toes
- press through you full front foot on the way up

Follow our program where fitness meets aesthetic:
@feroce_fitness_

node.text:
🔥Minimal equipment @feroce_fitness_ workout 🔥

✅ 5 sets
4 minutes amrap (as many reps as possible)
10 hang snatch + 1 arm push press each arm
10 squat knee to elbow 
Rest 1 minute between set

Bodybuilding portion:

✅ 4 sets
8x 1 leg deadlift/leg
rest as needed between 

Note: focus on your balance and keeping your back arch and your hip square. Slow down and control is the name of the game

✅ 4 sets
15 bent over flys double contraction 
directly into
20 bent over row (2 sec up/ 2 sec down)
rest 2 min between sets

Note: the bent over flys act as pre-fatigue so we can recruit more muscles fibers during the bent over row. Make sure to enjoy the burn and really drive your elbow back during the bent over row to bring the weight up and not so much on bending the elbow itself. You should be feeling you back muscles.

✅ 3 sets
Bulgarian split squat death set
8 heavy reps
8 sec hold
8 medium heavy reps
8 sec hold
8 light reps
8 sec reps
rest 2 minutes between sets 

Note: the total amount of work per set is 24 reps and 24 sec of holding.

node.text:
I am so incredibly proud of my twin sister @rachelleblancbazinet ! She can officially call herself an Olympian.

I’ve known her longer than anyone else in the world 😝 and I know how hard this road has been. Not only to qualify a year ago but have to go through the ups and down of training in isolation, not having or being allowed to train part of the year, dealing with the mental toll that isolation during covid can bring and the extra injuries that comes with having to push your body for an extra year to maintain your Olympic spot!

I only hoped that she would enjoy herself there and make memories that she worked so hard to deserve and she did just that with her amazing coach Yvan!!

Yay!!! ❤️❤️

This is my Go to post workout recovery + build muscle meal:

1 scoop of @nutrexresearch whey
1 cup of cocoa rice crispy 

Yes it’s a cereal bowl hahaha but instead of milk I use protein shake 😉🙌🏽

✅Rice cereal: easy digestible carbs and helps drive the protein Into the muscles

✅Whey Protein: helps recovery and muscle building

✅Low fat is important for a post workout because it slows down digestion and we want it to be high speed so the muscles absorb everything they need to grow and recover ASAP 

✅Chocolate flavor: because I’m obsessed with anything chocolate 🙌🏽

It’s so good and I get everything I want and need! Literally saving my life during this prep because I still feel like I am having some treat

node.text:
Photo/ video dump 🤪

“
It’s so fun to be practicing a new sport and saying it’s outside my comfort zone is an understatement. Funny enough performing in front of people use to give me so much anxiety that I would be sick in the bathroom every single time I would compete. Right before the first couple events I would just have to go and be shaking. It took me a couple years and a lot of mindset work to get that under control. I think part of pushing through my anxiety gave me a lot of confidence and the more I did it the stronger I felt.

In CrossFit I could focus on completing the task. Literally in 2010 after the first event, the other girls in my heat weren’t done and I went to ask if I could leave the floor 😂 I was so uncomfortable and the funny part is that there was about 200 spectators. 

Spending 3 months at the NICU this year and having more horribleness events in my life really put me back in a daily ocean of anxiety. 

I often feel paralyzed and pushing myself with a new goal surrounded by a strong plan that requires discipline and execution as been amazing for me. Thanks to @wattywatt01 for helping me with my prep and taking away all the thinking (because choosing is an anxious persons nightmare 😂)

I have been doing meditation and visualization to try to reduce the anxiety that comes with performing and showing myself again so here is my first step in showing you guys me practicing my routine 😬

Happy Birthday my sweet angel!

We spent the first 3 months of your life not knowing if you would have any birthday at all 😭😭

We are overwhelmed with love and Grateful beyond words ❤️

Cheers to an healthy baby and many more birthday 🎂

node.text:
Happy Birthday Zoe!!

I’ve been crying everyday for a week and I am quite an emotional mess… in all the best way possible!

When Zoe was born they told us she had a 50% chance of survival.
She couldn’t breath or feed on her own.

Every weeks for 12 weeks the doctors would tell us a new devastating thing about her and the test seemed to never be stopping:
- testing her heart because they hear something
- might need a transfusion because she is anemic
- there is bleeding in the brain
- swallowing X-ray to see why she has so much reflux
- and on and on

Our NICU journey felt like forever!!! oh boy I am over the moon that she is so perfect and beautiful and healthy.

I love her so much and I wish her to just shine as herself and keep being the sweetest most determined badass I know!!

Thank you again for all the kind words, thought and prayer sent our way during this thought time and thank you again to the hospital staff for being beyond wonderful

🔥Back and Abs 🔥

✅wide grip Seated row
Set 1- 20 reps
Set 2- 15 reps with 3 sec negative
Set 3- 12 heavy reps directly into 15 lighter reps
Set 4- 8 heavy reps directly into 12 reps
Set 5- 12 reps with 3 sec hold at the chest
Rest 60-90sec between sets

✅ lat pull down
Set 1- 15 reps
Set 2- 3x 3 slow reps (2sec up/2 sec down) into 5 fast reps … 24 reps total
Set 3- 3x 3 slow reps (2sec up/2 sec down) into 5 fast reps … 24 reps total
Set 4- 12 heavy reps into 15 lighter reps into 20 lighter reps
Rest 60 sec between sets

✅ Abs Finisher
4 rounds
20 knee raises
30 bicycle 
No rest here
